cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.MA, cs.CE 

This paper discusses a decision-making framework that combines classical multi-attribute utility theory with qualitative approaches for representing and reasoning about preferences. This work is relevant to the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) as it involves developing automated decision-making systems. The paper also involves data structures (cs.DS) and mathematical aspects (cs.MA) of decision theory. Finally, the paper discusses practical applications of decision-making systems (cs.CE).
